layerGroup.title: NESP Marine and Coastal Project 2.6 - Australian Sea Lions GPS tracks
layerGroup.abstractTxt: This map shows foraging trip summaries of eight adult female Australian Sea Lions tagged with GPS loggers and animal-borne cameras at Olive Island and Seal Bay, South Australia. Coloured lines show the foraging tracks of different individuals, traced between pings from satellite-linked GPS loggers that collected locations when the animals surfaced. Point size indicates the duration of high-definition video captured from forward-facing cameras glued to the animals' midline (larger points = longer video), while point colours show the likely degree of spatial approximation based on matching the video timestamps to the nearest recorded GPS location.
